Pastoralists and fishermen in Turkana have been warned of possible flash floods this week. The meteorology department has said areas around the Lake will experience heavy rains and warned residents to take caution. "Pastoralists and fishermen have been issued an advisory to avoid grazing along riverbeds and fishing at the Lake Turkana,"Â County Commissioner Seif Matata said on Sunday. Matata warned fishermen not fish at night as they may not be able to see the flashfloods headed to the Lake. "Last year we experienced heavy rains which caused flash floods in parts of Turkana which led to the death of people and many livestock. Most of the pastoralists lost their livestock as they were swept and killed by flash floods. Click here for the latest political news